# AdTruck Driver Native ‚Äî Cursor Rules

## What This App Does
This is a mobile app for truck drivers. Drivers log in with a username + password,
see their campaign for the day, start their shift, take a photo of their truck with
ad wrapping, submit it for approval, then end their shift. The app talks to a
Supabase backend shared with an admin web portal and a client web portal.

## Stack (exact versions matter ‚Äî do not assume latest)
- React Native + Expo SDK 54 (managed workflow), TypeScript strict mode
- Expo Router 6 (file-based routing ‚Äî folders and files become screens)
- Supabase (Postgres database + file storage + auth)
- Zustand (global auth state ONLY ‚Äî not for server data)
- TanStack Query v5 (server data fetching and caching)
- TanStack Form 1.27.7 (forms ‚Äî do NOT use react-hook-form)
- MMKV 4.x (local storage ‚Äî do NOT use AsyncStorage)
- NativeWind / Tailwind utility classes for styling
- Package manager: pnpm only (never npm or yarn)

